    <text id="B0394T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jordan inquires about the status of a case against six men.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient">J. Marshall McCue<lb/>Presiding Justice<lb/>Augusta
                        County, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-04-27">April 27, 1868.</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to request to be informed if the following named case has been
                    set for trial today and if not what condition the case is in at this date or
                    please furnish me with any information, touching the matter involved.</p>

                <p><abbr expan="Commonwealth">Comwth</abbr> of <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> vs.
                    Henry Fisher, William Ross, John Craig, Robt Craig, Wm Craig
                    (<unclear>Rvs</unclear> in <unclear>Summers</unclear>) and Abraham Ross.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully,<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient servant">obt. Svt.</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Jno W. Jordan<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A.Comr</abbr> &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
